=head1 NAME

hpxml - An openhpi sample application that displays system view in XML. 

=head1 SYNOPSIS 

hpixml [-D domain] [-s] [-i -t ]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

hpixml displays system view in XML.

If no domain is selected, hpixml uses a session with the default domain. The selected domain id must be configured via the openhpidclient.conf file specified in the environment.


=head1 OPTIONS

=over 2

 -D	"<arg>"	select domain id
 -s		display XML schema instead of XML
 -i		use indentation when displaying XML
 -t		use text names intsead of integer values when displaying enum and flag data


=back

